## Glossary

- **OT — Optical Table.** The top-down working surface; a grey plate,
  default 1.2 m × 2 m × 10 cm, resizable.
- **OE — Optical Element.** The basic placeable unit.
- **Active element.** The currently selected element; all editing acts
  on it and it is drawn distinctly.
- **Bounding box.** The A × A × B box that gives an element its size and
  orientation.
- **N1 / N2 — primary / secondary normal.** N1 is the element's face
  normal (R1 turns around it); N2 is its perpendicular reference. Unrotated,
  N1 lies along the CR and N2 along the table normal.
- **Drawer.** The function that draws an element from its placement point
  and three rotations; the first build uses one standard cylinder drawer.
- **LS — Light Source.** Emits the ray group; long and narrow.
- **D — Detector.** Terminates the ray group.
- **LP / CP — Linear / Circular Polarizer.** A polarizer regardless of
  where it sits on the bench.
- **S — Sample.** The material(s) under study.
- **RG — Ray Group.** One central ray plus eight side rays.
- **CR — Central Ray.** The main drawn ray.
- **RRG / TRG — Reflected / Transmitted Ray Group.**
- **IRG — Incident Ray Group.** The ray group falling on an element.
- **PP — Placement Point.** The point that snaps an element onto the CR.
- **R1 / R2 / R3.** The three element rotations. R1 turns around the
  surface normal (N1); R2 around the table normal; R3 around the third
  box axis. R3 is locked by default, and when R3 ≠ 0, R1 is no longer
  perpendicular to R2.
- **Element group.** One or more elements placed on or removed from the
  CR path as a unit.
- **Experiment collection.** A set of experiments around the same
  sample(s).
